Title: Where to look next and what to look for  
Author: Bernt Schiele and James L. Crowley 
Date: February 27, 1996  
Address: 46, Felix Viallet, 38031 Grenoble  
Affiliation: GRAVIR, I.N.P.G.,  
Abstract: In [Sch 96c] we have introduced the use of Multidimensional Receptive Field Histograms for Probabilistic Object Recognition. In this paper we reverse the object recognition problem by asking the question, "where should we look?", when we want to verify the presence of an object, to track an object or to actively explore a scene. This paper describes the statistical framework from which we obtain a network of salient points for an object. This network of salient points may be used for fixation control in the context of active object recognition. 
