Reference-contexts: 1 Introduction One of the important questions for fixation control in an active vision system is signified by the phrase "where to look next?" <ref> [Swa 93] </ref>. One can divide the different approaches for this problem into three categories: task driven, context driven and feature driven attention mechanisms. In this paper we propose a new statistical approach to answer the question "where to look next?".
